Many Ethereum Layer 2 solutions—such as Optimism (OP), Arbitrum (ARB), and zkSync (ZK)—have issued their own governance or utility tokens. These tokens often serve functions like network governance, staking, or providing incentives for ecosystem growth.

Base, however, launched without a native token, instead emphasizing security, scalability, and seamless integration with Coinbase’s broader ecosystem. The lack of a token has only intensified speculation that an eventual launch could be significant.
